	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.19]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Stay by the guards until level 4. Stay in the zone with guards at gate 'til level 5. At level 5, go to Qeynos hills. Watch out for Pyzjin or however her name is spelled, and for a roaming male necro whose name I can't recall. At level 7, kill the gnoll watchers, at 7+ go to Blackburrow, join a group and become a killing machine. At level 10, Everfrost also becomes a very fun zone that you can stay in 'til level 20 if you're so inclined. <br><br>West Karana becomes reasonable at level 10, once you hit 12 you can kill bandits. At 16 you really start having a world of options before you, including High Pass. <br><br>Some other places:<br><br>At level 9, the Warrens in Erudin becomes fun. You can level there until roughly 20. After that head you could head to Stonebrunt too. Both zones have great exp bonuses. <br><br>Some people head to Kunark at level 16 and fight in Lake of Ill Omen. I don't reccomend it until at least 19, if not 20.<br><br>Faydwer is very crowded but you can almost always find a partner in any zone. You can always go to Crushbone from level 7 on until about level 14-16. <br><br>Estate of Unrest is interesting but stay in a group and have lots of bat wings to travel back and forth through Dagnor's Cauldron. It can be a good place to hunt from the mid-teens on. Be sure to look at a map before you go to Unrest and discuss strategy first as you WILL die in Unrest if you don't have a good group leader or have an idiot in your group. I don't recommend soloing in Unrest unless you really know what you're doing.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dienia Tallis - Druid<br>Baila - retired Shaman<br>Addria - Enchanter<br>Iantha - Cleric<br>Phedre - Rogue<br>Pyria - Wizard</td></tr>
