	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 21st 11:48 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>IMHO the true advantages of being a Wizard over any of the other casting classes are as follows: (for normal play and not PvP)<br><br>Faster casting time - speed, chain casting, no one does it better than a wizard.<br>Major Nukes over all three types of magic - no other class has this. Also wizards get the big nukes sooner than the other classes (correct if this is wrong but from my research I feel this a true statement).<br>Nuke Damage - There is a debte here that other class can "out nuke" a Wizard. Unclear is the definition of "out nuke". Does that mean more damage for one spell or the total damage for the amount of mana used? True, there are some other classes spells that do about the same damage as a Wizards BUT at a much higher mana cost. So, a Wizard with the same mana count as a Mage would be able to "out nuke" the mage because the Wizards nukes are more mana efficient (not including specialization). Please, this is not a slam on mages but a truth. A wizard has the abilty to be a very powerful ally in a group if played to it's potential.<br>Porting-I can be just about anywhere I need to be in a matter of seconds/minutes. No boat for me! A great money maker. You will never hear of a poor wizard with this ability. Granted Druids get porting as well but they are Second to wizards in ability (there are just more of them). Ever hear of a Druid porting to the plane of Hate?<br>Evac's - Evacuate your party to safety. A nessecity for those plane raids. Your party will love you when you pull them out of deaths grip. Kinda like Scotty saving Kirk at the last second.<br><br>Dissadvantages to other casting classes. No pet for soloing or protecting you when medding. Face it, to solo as a wizard is a tough thing. alot of skill/stragedy and kahuna's are needed. I don't play EQ solo anymore and haven't soloed since the 8th level. I enjoy the groups and find the social group enviroment fun and exciting. Most classes can't solo that well anyway. Yes, even tanks need to slow down to heal. That's just the way the game was designed, for the group. Only one buff that is really bad O'keils Rad wears off too fast. Some groups will frown on a wizard for not being able to buff. There is also a misunderstanding amoungst the other classes about a wizard. Wizards are kinda like the kid thats picked last for the kickball team. Don't fret, this will not be the case as you grow in power. Once other players see the nukability of a wizard in action you will be indemand. I once joined 2 tanks a driud and another wizard in a group. The other wiz and myself took turns chain casting while the other med. the group was amazed at the exp we gained and the damage we did in such a short time. Our "healing" druid was getting bored since he really had nothing to do. We dropped the mobs to fast for them to do any real damage to the tanks.<br><br>But be forwarned!&nbsp;&nbsp;Many players give up and go on to other classes. Most are the one's that say "Wizards suck". Frustrated with thier own inability they blame the class. A wizard is not tougher. You just have to know how to play one.<br><br>Good Luck!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
