	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here is what I would twink a Wizard out with in hind sight. All of this stuff can be easily aquired at 30 or less, or bought fairly cheaply. No uber gear, but a good start. I'll list the zone, spawn, and estimated retail price.<br><br>Upper Guk<br><br>Froglock Scryer<br>2 bracelets of woven Grass (15-25pp)<br><br>Ancient Croc *if you can get the camp<br>1 gatorscale sleeve (500pp)<br>1 gatorscale legging (700pp)<br><br>Najena<br><br>Najena<br>1 Flowing black Silk Robe (100p)<br>1 Black tome with silver runes (300-500pp)<br><br>Unrest<br><br>Reclusive Ghoul Magi<br>1 Savants Cap (30p)<br>1 Bloodstained Gloves (?)<br><br>Permafrost<br><br>Goblin Scryer<br>1 Fur lined Slippers (?)<br>1 Staff (procs shock of frost) (?)<br><br>Two low level quest pieces are also nice. The Froglock Skin Mask, and black lace silk sash. Both you will need to pay a low level character for. The mask is a low level Troll Sk quest reward. The sash is from a quest in Paineel, but thanks to the trivial loot code, you need to be about 20 to complete it.<br><br>Jewelry I would recomend the basic +2 int rings, and a pair of polished bone hoops (10P) off Evil eyes in the gorge. <br><br>You already have a neclace and a cloak. Hope this helps!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
