	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a Wizard of the 31st Season and recently ventured to Velious. I went with a Druid friend (higher level, 37 I think) and a fellow Wizard (unsure about his level, was yellow con to me) to the Eastern Wastes, where we killed Snow Dervishes, Ulthork Warriors and Hunters, Snow Cougars and some Mammoths. The xp you get there is really awesome!<br>And we used a really simple tactic: <br>We all got SoW from the Druid, then Druid pulled one or two mobs, snared them. Then we Wizards used our Staff of Temperate Flux to reduce their fire resist and began nuking them. The Druid would DoT and Root one of the mobs. We Wizards concentrated on the other. Druid controlled the mobs so they did not get into melee range (renewing Snare and Root). <br>Even only with this Druid I was able to get a huge mass of xp there. Try it, but you definately need SoW...<br><br><br>Callissa Gatecaller<br>Mistress of the Arcane, Scholar of 8th Circle<br>Webmaster and Officer of Refiner's Fire<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
