	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100040368372192><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100040368372192>Get your Journeyman Boots. Now.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100040368372192#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 13th 1:54 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Get Journeyman Boots as early in the game as you can.&nbsp;&nbsp;No joke.  Do it.  None of that Traveller's Boots crap, either...  Find yourself a friend and camp the cyclops in OOT.  You are a failure as a wizard, otherwise.<br><br>Why is this?  Because Journeyman Boots are the Step; yes, the Step -- That being that once you put those little babies on, you are self sufficient.  No need for anyone to heal you; you can outrun everything.  No need to ask for SoWs; you have a run-while-casting effect that's much better for kiting.<br><br>Once you have JBoots, around level 35, start soloing Hill Giants with your AoE Snare spell that no one ever seems to use.  Don't give me any crap about not having enough mana or getting resisted too much -- if you fail, zone, and do it again.  With the money you make, buy some mana or INT equipment, and make it look pretty.  You want to look your best so people will fear you when you unleash the fury that is, "A Wizard begins to walk faster."<br><br>Now, get to level 44.  Buy Conflaguration.  Go to the Dreadlands.  Level to 50 in three days.  Level 45 will NOT take you a year to get out of, unless you have been lazy up to this point, going without JBoots.  You can kill just about anything in Dreadlands BY YOURSELF, and make a good bit of money from doing so in the process.<br><br>Now that you're 50, you BETTER have Ice comet, and you're on your way to those precious Lure spells.  Find a good guild, if you don't already have one, join it, and show them the meaning of "Magical damage".<br><br>Then kiss your JBoots, which got you there.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
