	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with you to a point.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, jboots aren't everything.  I've successfully soloed almost my entire carerr as a wizard without them.  snare is great, if it gets resisted, you've got your skin line of spells to help you take blows until you get a stun off.  After stun, you can root and back up, free to cast snare until it sticks. Once you do this, it's smooth sailing.  And to people who say that this won't work and that wizzies fall in 3 hits, it's not true, and this method is battle tested and proven, I solo reds on a regular basis @ 44 with few close calls.  You can't argue with success.<br><br>just my humble opinion<br>Knyo Mapshifter<br>wizard of the 46 circle<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
