	   <a name=100067197766454></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100067197766454><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100067197766454>RE: Sir Lag-a-Lot</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100067197766454#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=45423><span id= >gnain</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>27 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Sep 16th 4:26 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When I hit about lvl 16 I went to Nek, at the zone tunnel to Lavastorm, and camped the inkie guards who spawn just south of the big rock just south of that tunnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;To get there you should invis yourself, and run fast to the lavastorm zone.  The guards pop rate is just about the time it takes to med up.  If a stone guardian (or worse, an iron guardian) joins in the fray, run right away to the lavastorm zone, it's real close.   Each guard drops a bronze weapon, which sells for about 2 1/2 pp at the gypsies not far from the lavastorm entrance to nek.  I just invised myself to sneak up on the guard, and rooted and shooted from as far away as possible.  Also a good idea to invis yourself, at least at first, to run up to gypsies.  Of course if you are inkie yourself this not a good idea, but for me (gnome) was just fine, and do not worry that your killing the guards is gonna bother the inkie newbies (they do not seem to like the guards that much themselves, and none of them are hunting there anyways, so they do not rely on them--unlike the guards at the tollbooth in WC, often hunted by inkies, whose absence is often resented by peeps hunting there);  be sure to get good map of nek and lavastorm to orient yourself.  Do NOT try hunting the guards furthur south, by the bridge in Nek--too far from a nice zone, and higher level guards there.<br>At 19 or 20 the exp falls off and you might consider going to Lake Rathe and trying the aviak guards in the two towers on either side of the arena entrance--you can pull one at a time, and tho rarely the one on your left (as you face out from the tunnel) is joined by a pesky low lvl aviak who will interupt you, generally it is quite safe.  It IS polite to shout out a camp check just after zoning into Lake Rathe, to make sure no one is already camping there, but there is room for two, each one taking a tower.  In a good group you can also try the "escalator" on the island more or less due east of the areana zone, but there is a nasty lvl 25 aquagoblin who spawns there. No faction hits.  No trains.<br>But speaking of faction, if you do send your faction with the inkies spiralling down by killing the guards I mentioned at the top of this post, watch out for Dragoon Zytl in WC thereafter.  I spent a long time, lvls 11-14, hunting wisps at the tollbooth there, and never a problem;  then, after killing about 100 inkie guards, for some reason the ol Dragoon took a dislike to me and snuck up on me (to my great surprise) and killed me before I had time to realize what was up, just after I ported myself to the wizzie platform just east of the lake in WCommons.  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
