	   <tr><td colspan=2>I can attest to this! Wizards have a little problem finding groups. Why is this? I think it is a result of who starts a group. Lets say a Warrior. As a a warrior, your first priority is getting a cleric. 2nd priority is getting some more melee damage dealers. After that, you are going to want a 2ndary healer/buffer. Insert druid or shaman, and then put in a chanter for clarity, buffs, and crowd control. No room for us.<br><br>The groups we do get into are usualy full of the other left overs, and often make for an interesting group. The plus side though, is that we can solo yellws about as easily as we can blues and blacks. Just be careful when a mob goes resist crazy, and always have an escape rout handy.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
